<doc>
  <member name="MFCameraOcclusionState">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies the occlusion state of a camera.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>A value from this enumeration is returned by <see cref="IMFCameraOcclusionStateReport.GetOcclusionState" />. To get the occlusion states that are supported on the current device, and therefore may be returned by <b>GetOcclusionState</b>, call <see cref="IMFCameraOcclusionStateMonitor.GetSupportedStates" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso cref="IMFCameraOcclusionStateReport.GetOcclusionState" />
    <seealso cref="IMFCameraOcclusionStateMonitor.GetSupportedStates" />
  </member>
  <member name="MFCameraOcclusionState.MFCameraOcclusionState_Open">
    <summary>
      <para>The camera is not occluded.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="MFCameraOcclusionState.MFCameraOcclusionState_OccludedByLid">
    <summary>
      <para>The camera is occluded by the lid of the device.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="MFCameraOcclusionState.MFCameraOcclusionState_OccludedByCameraHardware">
    <summary>
      <para>The camera is occluded by camera hardware.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>